Using 200mm x 75mm sleepers, cut 6 lengths 2700mm long and 6 lengths 1500mm long. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/50/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/50/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Pre-paint the sleeper to minimise leeching of the chemical treatment. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/72/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/72/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Set the first string of sleepers 100mm into the soil using a 2700mm length on each side and 1500mm length on each end. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f2/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f2/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Join them using 2 x 125mm bugle head galvanised wood screws at each corner. Make sure they are level with a gauge. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/42/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/42/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Their external measurement should be 2700mm x 1650mm. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/65/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/65/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet5.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Repeat this for levels 2 and 3 of the wall so that the total depth is 600mm. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/93/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet6.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet6.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/93/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet6.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet6.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Tie the three levels together in each corner using 50mm x 50mm slotted galvanised angle and 30mm button headed galvanised wood screws. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/73/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet7.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet7.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/73/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet7.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-1Bullet7.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Place these plastic liners in the bed one at a time making sure the corners are not folded too tightly. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e7/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e7/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Take great care to avoid potential damage and leaks when the tank is filled with water. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7d/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7d/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Lay a 50mm slotted irrigation pipe around the inside perimeter of the bed to provide rapid distribution of water in the tank when it is being filled. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7e/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7e/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cut the filler tube (700mm long), vertical overflow tube (about 230mm long) and horizontal overflow tube (150mm) from a length of 40mm rigid PVC tube. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c3/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c3/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Using 3 way couplers, join them into the distribution pipe. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d5/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d5/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Secure the filler pipe to the bed wall using galvanised saddle clamps and 30mm button head galvanised wood screws (above the overflow point). {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9a/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9a/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Drill a 50mm hole through the bed wall just above the 250mm depth of the water tank. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7a/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7a/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet5.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Fit a 90 deg angle rigid PVC tube to the top of the overflow tube, and then connect the last piece of tube to the other end of the angle. Push this tube though the bed wall to provide an overflow route out of the bed. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/34/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet6.jpg/v4-460px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet6.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/34/Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet6.jpg/v4-760px-Build-a-Self%E2%80%90Feeding-Self%E2%80%90Watering-Garden-Bed-Step-4Bullet6.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
